HEADWORD: Irrespirable
<hw>Ir*res"pi*ra*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>irrespirabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>irrespirable</ets>. See
<er>Respirable</er>.]</ety> <def>Unfit for respiration; not having the
qualities necessary to support animal life; <as>as,
<ex>irrespirable</ex> air</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

